<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Iran & Hezbollah — Daily Situation Report · 17 March 2026</title>
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/Chart.js/4.4.1/chart.umd.js"></script>
<style>
  :root {
    --bg:#ffffff; --bg2:#f5f4f0; --bg3:#eeecea;
    --text:#1a1a18; --text2:#6b6a64; --text3:#9c9a92;
    --border:rgba(60,58,50,0.15); --border2:rgba(60,58,50,0.28);
    --red-bg:#FCEBEB; --red-text:#791F1F; --red-row:rgba(196,58,58,0.07);
    --amber-bg:#FAEEDA; --amber-text:#633806; --amber-row:rgba(186,117,23,0.07);
    --blue-bg:#E6F1FB; --blue-text:#0C447C;
    --green-bg:#EAF3DE; --green-text:#27500A;
    --purple-bg:#EEEDFE; --purple-text:#3C3489;
    --radius:10px; --radius-sm:6px;
  }
  @media(prefers-color-scheme:dark){
    :root{
      --bg:#1e1e1c; --bg2:#272725; --bg3:#2a2a28;
      --text:#e8e6de; --text2:#a8a69e; --text3:#6e6c66;
      --border:rgba(200,198,190,0.12); --border2:rgba(200,198,190,0.22);
      --red-bg:#3a1a1a; --red-text:#f5a0a0; --red-row:rgba(196,58,58,0.15);
      --amber-bg:#3a2a0a; --amber-text:#f0c070; --amber-row:rgba(186,117,23,0.15);
      --blue-bg:#0c2540; --blue-text:#80bcf4;
      --green-bg:#102010; --green-text:#80c870;
      --purple-bg:#1e1c40; --purple-text:#b0a8f0;
    }
  }
  *{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
  body{font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,"Segoe UI",Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;background:var(--bg3);color:var(--text);font-size:14px;line-height:1.5;padding:24px 16px}
  .page{max-width:960px;margin:0 auto}

  .header{background:var(--bg);border:0.5px solid var(--border);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:1.2rem 1.5rem;margin-bottom:14px;display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;gap:16px}
  .header-left{flex:1}
  .rpt-title{font-size:20px;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:3px}
  .rpt-sub{font-size:11px;color:var(--text2)}
  .header-stamp{font-size:10px;color:var(--text3);text-align:right;white-space:nowrap;padding-top:2px;line-height:1.7}

  /* Status pill bar — sits directly under header */
  .pill-bar{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:7px;margin-bottom:1.2rem}
  .s-pill{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:5px;font-size:11px;font-weight:500;padding:5px 11px;border-radius:20px;border:0.5px solid transparent}
  .s-pill .dot{width:7px;height:7px;border-radius:50%;flex-shrink:0}
  .sp-red{background:var(--red-bg);color:var(--red-text);border-color:rgba(163,45,45,0.2)}.sp-red .dot{background:#C43A3A}
  .sp-amber{background:var(--amber-bg);color:var(--amber-text);border-color:rgba(133,79,11,0.2)}.sp-amber .dot{background:#BA7517}
  .sp-green{background:var(--green-bg);color:var(--green-text);border-color:rgba(59,109,17,0.2)}.sp-green .dot{background:#3B6D11}

  .section{font-size:10px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text3);margin:1.4rem 0 .5rem}
  .card{background:var(--bg);border:0.5px solid var(--border);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:1rem 1.2rem;margin-bottom:12px}
  .g3{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,minmax(0,1fr));gap:10px;margin-bottom:12px}
  .g2-dev{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,minmax(0,1fr));gap:10px;margin-bottom:12px}

  .metric{background:var(--bg2);border-radius:var(--radius-sm);padding:.8rem 1rem}
  .mlabel{font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-bottom:3px}
  .mval{font-size:22px;font-weight:600;line-height:1.1}
  .munit{font-size:11px;color:var(--text3);margin-top:2px}
  .mval.red{color:#A32D2D}.mval.amber{color:#854F0B}.mval.blue{color:#185FA5}
  @media(prefers-color-scheme:dark){.mval.red{color:#f07070}.mval.amber{color:#e0a040}.mval.blue{color:#60a0e0}}

  /* Executive summary — coloured left border per severity */
  .exec-list{list-style:none;padding:0}
  .exec-list li{display:flex;gap:10px;padding:8px 10px;border-bottom:0.5px solid var(--border);font-size:12px;line-height:1.6;border-left:3px solid transparent;margin-left:0}
  .exec-list li:last-child{border-bottom:none}
  .exec-list li.e-red{border-left-color:#C43A3A;background:rgba(196,58,58,0.04)}
  .exec-list li.e-amber{border-left-color:#BA7517;background:rgba(186,117,23,0.04)}
  .exec-list li.e-green{border-left-color:#3B6D11;background:rgba(59,109,17,0.04)}
  .exec-num{font-size:11px;font-weight:600;color:var(--text3);min-width:18px;padding-top:1px;flex-shrink:0}
  .exec-text{flex:1;color:var(--text)}
  .exec-text b{font-weight:600}
  .new-tag{display:inline-block;font-size:9px;font-weight:600;padding:1px 5px;border-radius:3px;background:var(--purple-bg);color:var(--purple-text);vertical-align:middle;margin-left:3px}

  .dev-card{background:var(--bg2);border-radius:var(--radius-sm);padding:.85rem 1rem}
  .dev-top{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:7px;margin-bottom:6px}
  .dev-label{font-size:12px;font-weight:600}
  .dev-status{font-size:10px;font-weight:600;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:20px;margin-left:auto;flex-shrink:0}
  .ds-red{background:var(--red-bg);color:var(--red-text)}
  .ds-amber{background:var(--amber-bg);color:var(--amber-text)}
  .ds-green{background:var(--green-bg);color:var(--green-text)}
  .ds-blue{background:var(--blue-bg);color:var(--blue-text)}
  .dev-body{font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.6}
  .dev-body b{color:var(--text);font-weight:600}

  .badge{display:inline-block;font-size:10px;font-weight:600;padding:2px 7px;border-radius:4px;vertical-align:middle;white-space:nowrap}
  .b-red{background:var(--red-bg);color:var(--red-text)}
  .b-amber{background:var(--amber-bg);color:var(--amber-text)}
  .b-blue{background:var(--blue-bg);color:var(--blue-text)}
  .b-green{background:var(--green-bg);color:var(--green-text)}

  .norm-row{display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:8px;padding:5px 0;border-bottom:0.5px solid var(--border);font-size:11px}
  .norm-row:last-child{border-bottom:none}
  .norm-indicator{min-width:150px;font-weight:600;padding-top:2px;flex-shrink:0}
  .norm-val{flex:1;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.4}

  .scroll-x{overflow-x:auto;padding-bottom:4px}
  .ctitle{font-size:13px;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:2px}
  .csub{font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-bottom:8px}
  .legend{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:10px;font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-bottom:8px}
  .leg{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:4px}
  .ld{width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:2px;flex-shrink:0}
  .chart-note{font-size:10px;color:var(--text3);margin-top:6px;line-height:1.5}

  .tab-bar{display:flex;gap:6px;margin-bottom:10px}
  .tab-btn{font-size:11px;font-weight:600;padding:5px 14px;border-radius:var(--radius-sm);border:0.5px solid var(--border2);background:transparent;color:var(--text2);cursor:pointer;transition:background .15s}
  .tab-btn.active{background:var(--bg2);color:var(--text)}
  .tab-pane{display:none}.tab-pane.active{display:block}

  table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:12px}
  th{font-size:10px;font-weight:600;color:var(--text2);text-align:left;padding:5px 8px;border-bottom:0.5px solid var(--border2)}
  .row-trigger{cursor:pointer;user-select:none}
  .row-trigger td{padding:5px 8px;border-bottom:0.5px solid var(--border);vertical-align:middle;line-height:1.35}
  .row-trigger:hover td{background:var(--bg2)}
  .row-detail{display:none}
  .row-detail.open{display:table-row}
  .row-detail td{padding:5px 10px 9px 28px;border-bottom:0.5px solid var(--border);font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.55;background:var(--bg2)}
  .toggle-icon{font-size:9px;color:var(--text3);margin-right:5px;display:inline-block;transition:transform .15s;width:10px}
  .toggle-icon.open{transform:rotate(90deg)}
  tr.hi-fatal .row-trigger td{background:var(--red-row)}
  tr.hi-fatal .row-detail td{background:rgba(196,58,58,0.04)}
  tr.hi-mass .row-trigger td{background:var(--amber-row)}
  tr.hi-mass .row-detail td{background:rgba(186,117,23,0.04)}

  .key-legend{display:flex;gap:14px;font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);margin-bottom:8px;flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:center}
  .key-swatch{display:inline-block;width:11px;height:11px;border-radius:2px;margin-right:3px;vertical-align:middle}

  .footer{font-size:10px;color:var(--text3);margin-top:16px;line-height:1.6;border-top:0.5px solid var(--border);padding-top:10px}

  @media(max-width:620px){.g3,.g2-dev{grid-template-columns:1fr}.header{flex-direction:column}.header-stamp{text-align:left}.pill-bar{gap:5px}}
  @media print{body{background:white;padding:0}.page{max-width:100%}}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="page">

  <!-- HEADER -->
  <div class="header">
    <div class="header-left">
      <div class="rpt-title">Iran &amp; Hezbollah — Attacks on Israel: Daily Situation Report</div>
      <div class="rpt-sub">28 February – 17 March 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Open Source Intelligence &nbsp;·&nbsp; IDF · Alma Research Center · ACLED · Times of Israel · Al Jazeera · Haaretz · Ops.Group · Flightradar24</div>
    </div>
    <div class="header-stamp">Issued: 17 Mar 2026<br>12:00 UTC+2<br>OPEN SOURCE ONLY</div>
  </div>

  <!-- STATUS PILL BAR -->
  <div class="pill-bar">
    <span class="s-pill sp-red"><span class="dot"></span>Iran: ~9 waves/day · active</span>
    <span class="s-pill sp-red"><span class="dot"></span>Hezbollah: ~30 waves/day · active</span>
    <span class="s-pill sp-red"><span class="dot"></span>Ground invasion: Lebanon — launched 16 Mar</span>
    <span class="s-pill sp-green"><span class="dot"></span>TLV: all flight caps lifted 17 Mar</span>
    <span class="s-pill sp-red"><span class="dot"></span>Ceasefire: no framework — Iran or Hzb</span>
    <span class="s-pill sp-amber"><span class="dot"></span>HFC: full activity — most regions</span>
  </div>

  <!-- EXECUTIVE SUMMARY -->
  <div class="section">Executive summary — stakeholder briefing · 17 Mar</div>
  <div class="card">
    <ul class="exec-list">
      <li class="e-red"><span class="exec-num">01</span><span class="exec-text"><b>Israel launches full ground invasion of southern Lebanon (16–17 Mar).</b> <span class="new-tag">NEW</span> IDF ground forces entered Lebanon on 16 Mar. Defence Minister Katz stated the operation may result in indefinite occupation of Lebanese territory. France, UK, Germany, Italy and Canada jointly warned of "devastating humanitarian consequences." IDF expanding operations on 17 Mar with forces deepening into south Lebanon.</span></li>
      <li class="e-red"><span class="exec-num">02</span><span class="exec-text"><b>Iran's National Security Chief and Basij commander killed overnight 16–17 Mar.</b> <span class="new-tag">NEW</span> Ali Larijani (NSC Secretary) and Gholamreza Soleimani (Basij commander) killed — the highest-profile assassinations since Khamenei on day 1. Retaliation risk elevated. No reduction in attack tempo observed following the kills; Iran continues ~9 waves/day.</span></li>
      <li class="e-amber"><span class="exec-num">03</span><span class="exec-text"><b>All Israeli airspace passenger caps lifted (17 Mar); key international carriers remain suspended until at least June.</b> <span class="new-tag">NEW</span> HFC full activity. All route caps removed. El Al general ticket sales reopen 21 Mar. United Airlines has extended suspension to at least 15 Jun. BA suspended to 1 Jun. EasyJet to October. Air France earliest 26 Mar. UAE closed airspace 16 Mar — Dubai Airport fuel tank struck by drone.</span></li>
      <li class="e-amber"><span class="exec-num">04</span><span class="exec-text"><b>Lebanon displacement surpasses 1 million; 15 Israeli civilians confirmed killed over 17 days.</b> <span class="new-tag">NEW</span> UNHCR: 1M+ displaced in Lebanon (one fifth of population). Cumulative Israeli civilian toll: 15 killed, 3,369+ wounded (Al Jazeera/Alma 17 Mar). ~40% of wounded are shelter-related. Cluster MRVs (~50% of Iranian salvos) cause area casualties regardless of interception — including 2 construction workers killed by sub-munitions in Yehud on 2 Mar.</span></li>
      <li class="e-green"><span class="exec-num">05</span><span class="exec-text"><b>HFC moves most of Israel to full activity; interception rates holding at 88–94%.</b> Schools open where shelter is reachable across most of the country from today. North border areas excluded (active combat). IDF: 70%+ of Iranian missile launchers neutralised; 7,600+ strikes on Iran since 28 Feb. Iran fire rate down 86% from war peak but no ceasefire framework — senior Iranian official (16 Mar): "no scenario for ceasefire at this stage."</span></li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- CUMULATIVE METRICS -->
  <div class="section">Period cumulative impact — 28 Feb to 17 Mar</div>
  <div class="g3">
    <div class="metric"><div class="mlabel">Israeli civilians killed</div><div class="mval red">15</div><div class="munit">+ 2 soldiers = 17 total · Al Jazeera/Alma</div></div>
    <div class="metric"><div class="mlabel">Israelis wounded</div><div class="mval amber">3,369+</div><div class="munit">updated 17 Mar · Al Jazeera tracker</div></div>
    <div class="metric"><div class="mlabel">Lebanon displaced</div><div class="mval blue">1M+</div><div class="munit">one fifth of population · UNHCR 17 Mar</div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="g3">
    <div class="metric"><div class="mlabel">Iran attack waves (total)</div><div class="mval">195+</div><div class="munit">~9/day · no sign of abating</div></div>
    <div class="metric"><div class="mlabel">Hezbollah attack waves</div><div class="mval">485+</div><div class="munit">since 2 Mar · Alma 16 Mar count</div></div>
    <div class="metric"><div class="mlabel">Cluster MRV share (Iran)</div><div class="mval amber">~50%</div><div class="munit">of Iranian ballistic salvos · IDF confirmed</div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- KEY DEVELOPMENTS -->
  <div class="section">Key developments snapshot — 17 March 2026</div>
  <div class="g2-dev">
    <div class="dev-card">
      <div class="dev-top"><span style="font-size:14px">🎯</span><span class="dev-label">Military situation</span><span class="dev-status ds-red">Major escalation</span></div>
      <div class="dev-body">
        <b>Ground invasion (16–17 Mar):</b> IDF ground forces entered Lebanon 16 Mar · Katz: may be indefinite, resembling Gaza · Evacuation notices across wider south Lebanon · European 5 nations condemn.<br>
        <b>Leadership kills (overnight 16–17 Mar):</b> Ali Larijani (Iran NSC chief) &amp; Gholamreza Soleimani (Basij commander) killed · Most senior kills since Khamenei on day 1 · Retaliation risk elevated.<br>
        <b>Iran/Hzb fire:</b> ~9 Iran waves/day · ~30 Hzb waves/day · No reduction post-kills · IDF: 70%+ Iranian launchers neutralised · 7,600+ strikes on Iran since 28 Feb.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="dev-card">
      <div class="dev-top"><span style="font-size:14px">✈️</span><span class="dev-label">Travel &amp; airspace</span><span class="dev-status ds-green">TLV caps lifted · intl. suspended</span></div>
      <div class="dev-body">
        <b>NEW 17 Mar:</b> All pax caps removed on all TLV routes · Duty-free resumes Wednesday · El Al general sales reopen 21 Mar · EASA CZIB expires 18 Mar (renewal pending).<br>
        <b>TLV operating:</b> El Al, Israir, Arkia, Air Haifa · No pax cap · Fares elevated.<br>
        <b>International suspended:</b> United to at least 15 Jun (NEW) · BA to 1 Jun · EasyJet to October · Air France earliest 26 Mar · Delta, Lufthansa — no dates.<br>
        <b>Regional (NEW 16 Mar):</b> UAE closed airspace · Dubai Airport fuel tank struck by drone · Jordan restricted · Lebanon closed.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="dev-card">
      <div class="dev-top"><span style="font-size:14px">🏥</span><span class="dev-label">Hospitals &amp; displacement</span><span class="dev-status ds-amber">Elevated</span></div>
      <div class="dev-body">
        <b>Israel casualties:</b> 15 civilians + 2 soldiers killed · 3,369+ wounded · ~40% shelter-related · Hospital ops underground since day 1 · Elective procedures suspended.<br>
        <b>Israel displaced:</b> 3,000+ from Tel Aviv, Bnei Brak, Ramat Gan, Petah Tikva, Beit Shemesh, Be'er Sheva · Family/hotels; no camps.<br>
        <b>Lebanon:</b> 1M+ displaced · 820+ killed in Lebanon (Israeli assault) · Ground invasion deepening south Lebanon displacement.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="dev-card">
      <div class="dev-top"><span style="font-size:14px">🏫</span><span class="dev-label">HFC guidelines</span><span class="dev-status ds-green">Full activity — most regions</span></div>
      <div class="dev-body">
        <b>NEW 17 Mar:</b> Full activity for most of Israel · Schools open where shelter reachable · Gatherings permitted · Active combat exclusions in border areas.<br>
        <b>Remaining restricted:</b> North Israel border (active ground combat) · Gaza envelope partial restrictions.<br>
        <b>Workplaces:</b> Open nationwide · Shelter condition in northern communities.<br>
        <b>Budget:</b> Knesset voting on raising deficit ceiling to 5.1% GDP + NIS 32B additional defence spending.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- NORMALISATION INDICATORS -->
  <div class="section">Normalisation indicators — 17 March 2026</div>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="norm-row"><span class="norm-indicator">Schools — most areas</span><span class="badge b-green" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-right:8px">Open</span><span class="norm-val">HFC full activity from 17 Mar. Open where shelter reachable. North border excluded.</span></div>
    <div class="norm-row"><span class="norm-indicator">Schools — north border</span><span class="badge b-red" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-right:8px">Closed</span><span class="norm-val">Active ground combat zone. IDF evacuation orders in south Lebanon border strip.</span></div>
    <div class="norm-row"><span class="norm-indicator">Workplaces</span><span class="badge b-green" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-right:8px">Open nationwide</span><span class="norm-val">No national restrictions. Shelter condition in north.</span></div>
    <div class="norm-row"><span class="norm-indicator">Flights — all routes <span class="new-tag">NEW</span></span><span class="badge b-green" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-right:8px">Caps lifted</span><span class="norm-val">All pax caps removed 17 Mar. El Al general sales reopen 21 Mar. Duty-free resumes Wednesday.</span></div>
    <div class="norm-row"><span class="norm-indicator">United Airlines <span class="new-tag">NEW</span></span><span class="badge b-red" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-right:8px">Suspended to 15 Jun</span><span class="norm-val">United extended TLV suspension to at least 15 Jun 2026 — longest published extension of any US carrier.</span></div>
    <div class="norm-row"><span class="norm-indicator">Flights — other intl.</span><span class="badge b-red" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-right:8px">Suspended</span><span class="norm-val">BA to 1 Jun · EasyJet to October · Air France earliest 26 Mar · Delta, Lufthansa — no dates · EASA CZIB expires 18 Mar (renewal pending).</span></div>
    <div class="norm-row"><span class="norm-indicator">Regional airspace <span class="new-tag">NEW</span></span><span class="badge b-red" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-right:8px">UAE closed</span><span class="norm-val">UAE closed airspace 16 Mar. Dubai Airport fuel tank struck by drone. Jordan restricted. Lebanon closed.</span></div>
    <div class="norm-row"><span class="norm-indicator">Iran fire tempo</span><span class="badge b-amber" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-right:8px">~9 waves/day</span><span class="norm-val">No reduction post-leadership kills. No ceasefire. IDF: "war may last several more weeks."</span></div>
    <div class="norm-row"><span class="norm-indicator">Ground war — Lebanon</span><span class="badge b-red" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-right:8px">Active invasion</span><span class="norm-val">IDF in Lebanon since 16 Mar. No ceasefire. France mediating. G5 leaders warning against escalation.</span></div>
    <div class="norm-row"><span class="norm-indicator">Iran ceasefire</span><span class="badge b-red" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-right:8px">No framework</span><span class="norm-val">Senior Iranian official (16 Mar): "no scenario for ceasefire at this stage." Tehran demands non-aggression guarantee.</span></div>
  </div>

  <!-- DAILY WAVES CHART -->
  <div class="section">Attack waves per day — Iran vs Hezbollah (28 Feb – 17 Mar)</div>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="ctitle">Daily attack waves on Israel (stacked by actor)</div>
    <div class="csub">Hezbollah joins 2 Mar. Waves = distinct coordinated salvos. Hover over each bar for actor split and munition type breakdown.</div>
    <div class="legend">
      <span class="leg"><span class="ld" style="background:#185FA5"></span>Iran</span>
      <span class="leg"><span class="ld" style="background:#C43A3A"></span>Hezbollah</span>
    </div>
    <div class="scroll-x"><div style="min-width:740px;position:relative;height:240px"><canvas id="dailyChart"></canvas></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- NEUTRALISATION CHART -->
  <div class="section">Daily interception rate — Iran vs Hezbollah (28 Feb – 17 Mar)</div>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="ctitle">Neutralisation rate by day &amp; actor (%)</div>
    <div class="csub">Iran rate generally higher due to longer intercept window. Hezbollah data from 2 Mar. ★ = significant impact despite high interception rate.</div>
    <div class="legend">
      <span class="leg"><span class="ld" style="background:#185FA5;border-radius:50%"></span>Iran intercept rate</span>
      <span class="leg"><span class="ld" style="background:#C43A3A;border-radius:50%"></span>Hezbollah intercept rate</span>
    </div>
    <div class="scroll-x"><div style="min-width:740px;position:relative;height:220px"><canvas id="neutChart"></canvas></div></div>
    <div class="chart-note">★ 1 Mar: Beit Shemesh 9 killed (cluster warhead) &nbsp;·&nbsp; ★ 4 Mar: Hzb peak, Haifa reached &nbsp;·&nbsp; ★ 9 Mar: Fateh-110 strikes Ramla &nbsp;·&nbsp; ★ 10 Mar: 2 killed ~200 wounded (cluster MRV) &nbsp;·&nbsp; ★ 13 Mar: Zarzir ~60 wounded (partial intercept)</div>
  </div>

  <!-- TABBED + COLLAPSIBLE IMPACT TABLES -->
  <div class="section">Impact analysis — direct hits vs interception debris &amp; shrapnel</div>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="key-legend">
      <span><span class="key-swatch" style="background:rgba(196,58,58,0.15);border:1px solid rgba(196,58,58,0.3)"></span>Red row = fatalities</span>
      <span><span class="key-swatch" style="background:rgba(186,117,23,0.1);border:1px solid rgba(186,117,23,0.25)"></span>Orange row = 20+ wounded</span>
      <span style="color:var(--text3);font-size:10px">&#9658; Click any row to expand full detail</span>
    </div>
